@Dsdfe: You can't reply with an image.
Otherwise you can post an image by clicking the `image` icon next to the text box when submitting a new post.
Except if you are on TorBrowser, than you'll get only white images. See [my post](/1MeFqFfFFGQfa1J3gJyYYUvb5Lksczq7nH/?Post/1oranGeS2xsKZ4jVsu9SVttzgkYXu4k9v/1DfrA2M9Qra6stqT6tzwNMYNweswY54KAC/1547399672) about it for more info.

@nekololi: It doesn't disable it, but rather makes it always return white pixels. This can be disabled by typing `about:config` in the address bar and setting `privacy.resistFingerprinting` to false.  
Beware however that this leaves you yourself wide open for a lot of correlation attacks that can be performed, on sites that you allow javascript to run on.  


On a sort of related note I'm working on a Tor Browser friendly ZeroMe client, where you don't have to disable `privacy.resistFingerprinting` at all.
